featured_reviews.review_id: It is the oldest mosque of Assam d is believed to be build  on the old solabeel area of purana Guwahati, presently known as ambari. It is believed an old man named Bura Baba has accompained the Mughal army during the first invasion of the ahom Kingdom in 1615. Following the treaty of Ghilajarighat, signed on January 23,1663, the Mughals under Mir Jhumla compelled the ajom King Jayadhwaj Singha to accept Delhi's vassalage and cede a large part of the territory of western Assam to the Mughals by virtue of which , parts of kamrup including Guwahati came under Mughal rule. Following the takeover of the city and appointment of Rashid khanas fauzdar if Guwahati, need was felt to construct a masjid for the soldiers to pray. It is also believed that bura baba settled in the same location where the masjid stands  and was buried there. Another version is that an old pious lady had gifted the land to construct the masjid. It draws a large crowds of people.
